com.linecorp.armeria.server

Interface Service<I extends Request,O extends Response>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    HttpService
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCompositeService, AbstractHttpService, AbstractTracingService, DecoratingService, DocService, DropwizardMetricCollectingService, HttpFileService, HttpHealthCheckService, HttpTracingService, JettyService, LogCollectingService, LoggingService, SimpleCompositeService, ThriftCallService, ThriftService, THttpService, TomcatService
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Service<I extends Request,O extends Response>
    Handles a request received by a Server.

      • as

        default <T extends Service<?,?>> Optional<T> as(Class<T> serviceType)
        Undecorates this Service to find the Service which is an instance of the specified serviceType. Use this method instead of an explicit downcast since most Services are decorated via decorate(Function) and thus cannot be downcast. For example: 
        
 Service s = new MyService().decorate(LoggingService::new).decorate(AuthService::new);
 MyService s1 = s.as(MyService.class);
 LoggingService s2 = s.as(LoggingService.class);
 AuthService s3 = s.as(AuthService.class);
        Parameters:
        serviceType - the type of the desired Service
        Returns:
        the Service which is an instance of serviceType if this Service decorated such a Service. Optional.empty() otherwise.
